main event: A bright, round, pinpoint of light was observed passing over Naha Air Base in Okinawa on June 6, 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 5 minutes, passing overhead at an altitude of approximately 1,000 feet.
The object was described as a bright, white, pinpoint of light, without any visible tail or wings.
The object moved across the sky slightly above the horizon to the southwest, in a less erratic manner than a typical star.
Attempts were made to obtain visual and photographic evidence, but the film quality was unsatisfactory and no distinct image was obtained.
No known activity or condition that could account for the sighting was identified, and no intercept or identification action was taken.
sighted object: a bright, round, pinpoint of light
photographs: yes, but the film quality was unsatisfactory
